it.emarolab.owloop.core

Interface ObjectProperty.Super<O,J,D extends ObjectProperty<O,J>>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the ontology.
    J - the type of Ground and EntitySet managed by this Descriptor.
    D - the type of the ObjectProperty descriptor instantiated during buildSuperObjectProperty() through getNewSuperObjectProperty(Object, Object).
    All Superinterfaces:
    Axiom, Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>, ObjectProperty<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ObjectPropertyExpression.Super<D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FullObjectPropertyDesc, HierarchicalObjectPropertyDesc
    Enclosing interface:
    ObjectProperty<O,J>

    public static interface ObjectProperty.Super<O,J,D extends ObjectProperty<O,J>>
extends ObjectProperty<O,J>
    Implementation of this interface enables a ObjectProperty to have the ObjectProperty.Super expression.

    • Method Detail

      • readExpressionAxioms

        default java.util.List<Axiom.MappingIntent> readExpressionAxioms()
        Description copied from interface: Axiom.Descriptor
        This method is used to update specific Axiom.EntitySet (or Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet) by synchronizing the internal state of the descriptor with the queried OWL structure, such that they are equal. It is based on EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet).
        Specified by:
        readExpressionAxioms in interface Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>
        Returns:
        the changes made in the Axiom.EntitySet during the reading. Note that the elements of the returned list, may not have the Axiom.MappingIntent.getOntologyChanges() field initialised (i.e.: Void).

      • buildSuperObjectProperty

        default java.util.Set<D> buildSuperObjectProperty()
        Create an Axiom.Descriptor set where each element represents the super object property of this property. Each of ObjectPropertys are instantiated through the method getNewSuperObjectProperty(Object, Object); this is called for all getSuperObjectProperties().
        Returns:
        the set of ObjectPropertys that describes the super relations of this described ontological property.

      • getNewSuperObjectProperty

        D getNewSuperObjectProperty(J instance,
                            O ontology)
        This method is called by buildSuperObjectProperty() and its purpose is to instantiate a new ObjectProperty to represent a super property of this ObjectProperty Descriptor.
        Parameters:
        instance - the instance to ground the new super ObjectProperty.
        ontology - the ontology in which ground the new ObjectProperty.
        Returns:
        a new Axiom.Descriptor for all the super properties of the one described by this interface.

      • querySuperObjectProperty

      • synchroniseSuperObjectPropertyToExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseSuperObjectPropertyToExpressionAxioms()
        It calls EntitySet#synchroniseTo(EntitySet) with querySuperObjectProperty() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed in the OWL representation for synchronise it with respect to getSuperObjectProperties(). This should be done by Axiom.Descriptor.writeExpressionAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise this structure with the super properties of Axiom.Descriptor.getInstance(); to the OWL representation.

      • synchroniseSuperObjectPropertyFromExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseSuperObjectPropertyFromExpressionAxioms()
        It calls ExpressionEntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet) with querySuperObjectProperty() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed into the getSuperObjectProperties() in order to synchronise it with respect to an OWL representation. This is be done by readExpressionAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise the super object properties of Axiom.Descriptor.getInstance(); from an OWL representation to this Descriptor.
